   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Follow this procedure to inspect for leaks on the MFC after replacement:</p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Inspect the MFC for any possible leaks after the burner is restarted.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Use soapy water.</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If a leak has occurred at the flange</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Tighten the flange bolts.</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Tools Required</b> Adjustable wrench, flange gaskets. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">If the leak continues:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Switch back to the spare gas and oxygen circuit.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Lockout tagout the leaking gas and oxygen circuit, and replace the flange
                     gasket.</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">After the burner is lit:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Go the display and press the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Logo</uicontrol> button to activate
                     the backlight.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Verify that the flow is within 5% of the setpoint. </li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_zjk_h5m_vcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image1.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_akk_h5m_vcc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Verify that the flow rates displayed on each MFC are at the setpoint valules on the DFC.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_bfr_35m_vcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_cfr_35m_vcc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If there is a deviation between the actual flow and the setpoint flow:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">There may be a possible line clog.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">The MFC may require maintenance or repair.</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In DFC, go to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Melter H3C</b> screen and click the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Comb. Skid
                  1</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Comb. Skid 2</uicontrol>, or <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Comb. Skid
                  3</uicontrol> tabs.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Verify that the line pressures are at similar values. </li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_wvl_p5m_vcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image3.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_xvl_p5m_vcc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If a line pressure is more than 0.35 bar (5.08 psi) higher than the other
               values:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Inspect for any possible clogged lines between the MFC and burner.</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
         </step>
      </steps>
